  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">STAR 2 - Accessible and quality mental health care</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1.Engaging and collaborating with MLGRD, MoF and MMDAs to improve/ increase resources committed to districts and across the country for mental health services
2.Strengthening voice, participation and influence of mental health service users and care-givers in mental health
3.Participatory monitoring to ensure effective utilisation of resources to enhance mental health service provision
4.Mobilise/ liaise with key actors facilitate spaces and advocate for relevant state institutions to ensure Parliament approves the draft LI</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The results of the project are as follows: (1) Increased budgetary allocations for community mental health care services in at least 30 targeted MMDAs; The 30 target districts are located in the northern-most regions of Ghana and the Brong-Ahafo Region. It is anticipated that with the national engagements with the MDAs will result in clear directives requiring of MMDAs to make budgetary allocations and have number activities to enhance mental health care services in the districts. (2) Improved access and quality community mental health care services at the district level (30 MMDAs) to the populations; an estimated 1500 (700F) women and men, girls and boys will be reached and benefiting from services. The estimated number of people to be reached will serve as good indicator to assessing their impression of the quality of services provided. A third result of this project is that there is (3) Enhanced public knowledge and awareness and amplified voice of mental service users.</narrative>
  </description>
